01:25:44.600 --> 01:25:47.720
But this large g which
we achieve in a cavity,

01:25:47.720 --> 01:25:51.540
if you put many
atoms in it, gets

01:25:51.540 --> 01:25:53.730
enhanced by the optical density.

01:25:53.730 --> 01:25:57.790
So the cavity enhancement and
the superradiant enhancement

01:25:57.790 --> 01:25:59.360
is multiplicative.

01:25:59.360 --> 01:26:03.110
And often, it's very favorable
for single photon manipulation

01:26:03.110 --> 01:26:03.930
if you do Bose.

01:26:03.930 --> 01:26:08.750
You getting enhancement form
the cavity and enhancement

01:26:08.750 --> 01:26:10.180
